      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 12,
      "mode": 0,
      "properties": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "MULTI-ANGLE PATCH - CALIBRATION PROOF\n\nThe LoRA angles are ABSOLUTE (subject-relative), NOT relative to your\nsource view. So set BOTH views on the Add Patch View node:\n  source_azimuth_view = what your source photo already is (front view\n    for a straight-on shot);  patch_*_view = what you asked the LoRA for\n    (must match the Qwen Multiangle Camera node exactly).\n  Orbit applied = patch - source.\n\n1. Generate a novel view at 'front-right quarter view / eye-level shot /\n   medium shot' (Qwen-Image-Edit-2511 + Multiple-Angles LoRA, e.g. via\n   ComfyUI-qwenmultiangle). Load it in the Patch novel view node.\n2. On Add Patch View keep patch_azimuth_view = 'front-right quarter view'\n   and source_azimuth_view = 'front view' (=> +45 deg orbit).\n3. Queue, then in the Atlas Viewport: Camera View, then Project.\n   GO/NO-GO: orbit slightly right - the patch should fill the primary's\n   occluded/grazing right side and stay aligned in the overlap. If it\n   lands on the WRONG side, tick flip_azimuth. If features line up,\n   constructed-orbit == LoRA-angle holds and the 3-patch build is safe.\n   (Needs a ComfyUI restart to load the new node + a browser refresh.)"
      ]
    }
